Effect.raceAll returns the result of whichever effect completes first — successfully or with a typed failure — and then interrupts every remaining candidate. Losers are never observed, so side effects in them run up to the interrupt boundary but their results are discarded. This makes raceAll safe for speculative fan-out where you only care about the winner.

